article.headline: Tennessee Tech 91, Southeast Missouri State 76
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Belton Rivers led Tennessee Tech with 33 points to give the Golden Eagles a 91-76 victory over Southeast Missouri Saturday night. Anthony Fischer also delivered for Tech with 19 points, Amadi McKenzie scored 12 points with 12 rebounds and Rashaud Nixon added another 10 points. The Golden Eagles raced to a 13-3 lead in the first four minutes of play, but southeast Missouri worked back to tie the game 28-28 with 7:06 to go before halftime. The Redhawks led 42-39 at the intermission. Tech was back on top a minute and a half into the second half with, but the Redhawks tied again 53-53 with 14:20 to go. A layup by Rivers started Tech on an 18-4 run that gave the Golden Eagles a lead it would not lose.
